title: Military Spokesman Says Israel Plans to Increase Strikes on Gaza
description: A military spokesman said Israel plans to step up its attacks on the Gaza Strip.

title: Bobby Charlton, Manchester United and England Soccer Great, Dies at 86
description: A gifted midfielder, Charlton was a leading scorer for Manchester United  and helped England win in the 1966 World Cup.

title: Javier Milei Is the Frontrunner in Argentina’s Presidential Race. Here’s What to Know
description: Milei shocked experts by winning a primary in August, launching him to the front of the race. Here's what you need to know.

title: Pakistan’s Self-Exiled Former Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif Returns Home Ahead of Vote
description: Pakistan's thrice-elected former Prime Minister returned home on a chartered plane from Dubai, after four years of self-imposed exile in UK.

title: Powerful Storm Hits Northern Europe, Killing at Least 4 People
description: A storm battered Britain, northern Germany and southern Scandinavia early Saturday, for a third day.

title: Egypt’s Border Crossing Opens to Let Desperately Needed Aid Into Besieged Gaza
description: Just 20 trucks were allowed in, an amount that aid workers said was insufficient to address the unprecedented humanitarian crisis in Gaza.

title: The Only Way to Fix Congress
description: The disaster over choosing a new Speaker has shown how broken the House truly is. Only serious election reform can heal it.

title: Inside the AI-Powered Race to Decode Ancient Roman Scrolls
description: A college student seeking a $1 million prize used AI to decode part of a 2,000-year-old scroll buried by the eruption of Mount Vesuvius.
